properties.name: Grant Park
properties.description: Grant Park’s street address is 337 East Randolph St. in Chicago, IL.  The park is bounded on the north by Randolph Dr. and the Chicago River, on the east by Lake Michigan, on the south by McFetridge Dr., and on the west by Michigan Ave.  The park is open Monday-Friday 9:00am to 10:00pm and Saturday and Sunday 9:00am to 5:00pm, and is wheelchair accessible.  Call 312-742-7648 for information or visit the Chicago Park District Grant Park website.

properties.name: Lou Mitchell's Restaurant
properties.description: 565 West Jackson Boulevard, Chicago, IL. 60661, 312-939-3111, Open Monday-Saturday 5:30am to 3:00pm, Sunday 7:00am to 3:00pm for breakfast and lunch.

properties.name: Dell Rhea's Chicken Basket
properties.description: 645 Joliet Road, Westillowbrook (Hinsdale), IL. 60527, 630-325-0780, Open Sun, Tues-Thurs 11am-9pm, Fri-Sat 11am-10pm

properties.name: Ambler's Texaco Gas Station
properties.description: Ambler's Texaco Gas Station, now the Village of Dwight's Visitor's Center, is located at the northeast corner of Old Route 66 and Illinois Route 17 in Dwight, IL., 217-788-1511

properties.name: Standard Oil Gas Station
properties.description: The Standard Oil Gas Station is located at 400 S. West St. in Odell, IL. Owned by the Village of Odell, the station is open daily 11:00am to 3:00pm for tours and as a visitor center. Contact Odell Tourism and Community Development for information at 815-998-2133.

properties.name: Illinois State Police Office
properties.description: The Illinois State Police Office is located at 15551 Old Route 66 between East 1500 North Road and East 1400 North Road in Pontiac, IL.  The building is not open to the public.

properties.name: Sprague's Super Service
properties.description: Sprague’s Super Service is located at 305 East Pine Street in Normal, IL. and is currently used as a private residence.

properties.name: Downey Building
properties.description: The Downey Building is at 110 and 112 Southwest Arch Street in Atlanta, IL. The Palms Grill is at 110 Southwest Arch Street, and is open Sunday-Thursday 8:00am to 5:00pm and Friday and Saturday 8:00am to 8:00pm, and is wheelchair accessible. Call 217-648-2233 for information or visit the Palms Grill Cafe website.  The Atlanta Museum is at 112 Southwest Arch Street, and is open Monday-Saturday 9:00am to 4:30pm. The first floor is wheelchair accessible and the museum is free. Call the Atlanta Public Library at 217-648-2112 or the Palms Grill for information.

properties.name: Ariston Cafe
properties.description: 413 Old Route 66 North Litchfield, IL. 62056, 217-324-2023, Mon - Fri 11am- 10pm, Sat 4-10pm, Sun 11am - 9pm

properties.name: Belvidere Cafe, Motel, and Gas Station
properties.description: The Belvidere Café, Motel, and Gas Station is located at 817 Old Route 66 in Litchfield, IL.  Much of the complex is out of use, but motel rooms are rented nightly for approximately $29 and are accessible to wheelchairs.  Call 217-324-4411 for more information.

properties.name: Soulsby Service Station
properties.description: 710 West 1st S Street, Mt Olive, IL. 62069

properties.name: Chain of Rocks Bridge
properties.description: Chain of Rocks Bridge parallels U. South 270 along Westest Chain of Rocks Road between Riverview Drive in Saint Louis, MO and Illinois 3 in Madison County, IL.  Connections are present to the MCT Confluence Trail, Mississippi River Trail, and Street Louis Riverfront Trail, and free parking is available in Illinois at the bridge entrance and at North Riverfront Park, south of the bridge along the Riverfront Trail.  The bridge is open to bikers and pedestrians daily from 9:00am to dusk and is wheelchair accessible.  Call 314-416-9930.

properties.name: Meramec River US 66 Bridge
properties.description: The Meramec River U.South 66 Bridge is located approximately two miles east of Eastureka, MO, within the Route 66 State Park along the historic alignment of Route 66.

properties.name: Big Chief Restaurant
properties.description: The Big Chief Restaurant building, now occupied by the Big Chief Roadhouse is at 17352 Old Manchester Road in Wildwood, MO.  The restaurant is open Monday 4:00pm to 10:00pm, Tuesday-Friday 11:00am to 11:00pm, and Saturday and Sunday 7:00am to 11:00pm, and is wheelchair accessible.   Call 636-458-3200 for information.

properties.name: Red Cedar Inn
properties.description: The Red Cedar Inn is located at 1047 East Osage Street in Pacific, MO.  The restaurant closed in 2005 and is not open to the public to visit but can be viewed from the road.

properties.name: Wagon Wheel Motel
properties.description: 901-905 East Washington Street, Cuba,MO.,65453, 573-885-3411

properties.name: Pulaski County Courthouse
properties.description: The Pulaski County Courthouse is located on Old Route 66 on the Courthouse Square, between Benton and North Lynn Streets in Waynesville, IL.

properties.name: Gillioz Theatre
properties.description: 325 East Park Central East Street, Springfield, MO 65806

properties.name: Rock Fountain Court
properties.description: The Rock Fountain Court is located at 2400 West College Street in Springfield, Mo. It is not open to the public.

properties.name: 66 Drive-In
properties.description: The 66 Drive-In is located at 17231 Old Route 66 Boulevard in Carthage (Brooklyn Heights), MO and offers first run feature films every Friday through Sunday, from April to October.  The Box Office opens at 8:00pm.

properties.name: Kansas Route 66-Eastast Galena Historic District
properties.description: The Kansas Route 66 Historic District-East Galena is located along Main Street in Galena, KS. To follow the oldest alignment of Route 66 through the Kansas Route 66 Historic District-East Galena, travel west out of Joplin, Missouri on 7th Street and enter Galena from the north end of town, then make a sharp left turn onto Main Street.

properties.name: Kansas Route 66-Eastast Galena Historic District
properties.description: The Kansas Route 66 Historic District-East Galena is located along Main Street in Galena, KS. To follow the oldest alignment of Route 66 through the Kansas Route 66 Historic District-East Galena, travel west out of Joplin, Missouri on 7th Street and enter Galena from the north end of town, then make a sharp left turn onto Main Street.

properties.name: Williams' Store
properties.description: The Williams' Store, now the Eisler Brothers Old Riverton Store, is located at 7109 SE Highway 66 in Riverton, KS. The store is open for business Monday-Saturday 9:00am to 3:30pm. For further information, please contact the store at 620-848-333

properties.name: Brush Creek Bridge
properties.description: The Brush Creek Bridge can be reached by driving north on N. Willow Ave. (Southeast 50th) approximately 3.5 miles out of Baxter Springs, Kansas.

properties.name: Baxter Springs Station
properties.description: The Baxter Springs Independent Oil and Gas Service Station building is at 940 Military Avenue in Baxter Springs, Kansas. The building now houses the Route 66 Visitor’s Center, which is open to the public Monday-Saturday, 10:00am to 5:00pm.  Call 620-856-2066 for information.

properties.name: Coleman Theatre
properties.description: The Coleman Theatre is located at the corner of 1st and Main Streets in downtown Miami, Oklahoma. It remains an important entertainment and commercial center for the community and is a popular stop for travelers along Route 66. The theatre offers free tours Tuesday through Friday, from 10:00am to 4:00pm, and 10:00am to 12:00pm on Saturdays.

properties.name: Miami Marathon Oil Company Service Station
properties.description: 331 South Main Street, Miami, OK 74354

properties.name: Chelsea Motel
properties.description: The Chelsea Hotel is at the intersection of Historic Route 66, called North Walnut Avenue, locally, and East First Street in Chelsea, Oklahoma.  The motel is privately owned and used for storage.  It is not accessible to the public but can be viewed from the public right of way.

properties.name: Ed Galloway's Totem Pole Park
properties.description: On Oklahoma State Highway 28A, at a point 3.5 miles east of US Route 66.  The junction of these two roads occurs in the center of Foyil, Oklahoma.  The park and its gift shop are open to the public Monday-Saturday 11:00am to 3:00pm and Sunday 12:30pm to 4:00pm.

properties.name: Vickery Phillips 66 Station
properties.description: The Vickery Phillips 66 Station is located at 602 S. Elgin Ave. on the southwest corner of 6th and Elgin Sts. facing north toward 6th St. in Tulsa, OK. Visitors are welcome at the station, which now operates as an Avis Rental Car field office. For information call 918-582-2534.

properties.name: 11th Street Arkansas River Bridge
properties.description: The 11th Street Arkansas River Bridge spans the Arkansas River on historic Route 66 between the Southwest Boulevard Bridge and Interstate 244 Bridge.

properties.name: Bridge #18 at Rock Creek
properties.description: Bridge #18 at Rock Creek is still in use as the part of Historic Route 66 crossing Rock Creek in Sapulpa, Oklahoma.

properties.name: Rock Cafe
properties.description: The Rock Café is located at 114 W. Main St. in Stroud, OK. The café is open from 6:00am to 9:00pm seven days a week.  For information, call 918-968-3990.

properties.name: Seaba Station
properties.description: The Seaba Station is located on the north side of Route 66 eight miles west of Chandler, OK  near the community of Warwick. It is also one mile east of Highway 177.  The station is currently open Monday, Tuesday, Thursday from 10:00am to 5:00pm, and Friday to Sunday from 10:00am to 6:00pm. For more information call 405-258-9141

properties.name: Chandler Armory
properties.description: The Chandler Armory at 400 East Route 66 in Chandler, OK now houses the Route 66 Interpretive Center and Gift Shop. The center is open from 10:00am to 5:00pm every day April-August and Tuesday-Saturday September-March and is almost entirely wheelchair accessible. Call 405-258-1300 for information

properties.name: Threatt Filing Station
properties.description: The Threatt Filling Station is at the intersection of Historic Route 66 and Northorth Pottawatomi Road in Luther, OK. It is closed to the public and may be viewed from the road.

properties.name: Arcadia Round Barn
properties.description: The Arcadia Round Barn is located in Arcadia, OK.  Turn east off Interstate 35 at Route 66 and travel six miles.  Admission is free.  The barn is open 7 days a week from 10:00am to 5:00pm. The upstairs loft can be reserved for special events. For information, call 405-396-0824

properties.name: Milk Bottle Grocery
properties.description: The Milk Bottle Grocery is located at 2426 North Classen Blvd in northwestern Oklahoma City, OK.

properties.name: Lake Overholser Bridge
properties.description: Lake Overholser Bridge carries local traffic as part of North Overholser Drive and is half a mile west of Council Road in Oklahoma City, OK.

properties.name: Avant's Cities Service Station
properties.description: The Avant’s Cities Service Station is located at 220 N. Choctaw, and the Jackson Conoco Service Station is located at 121 W. Wade in El Reno, OK.

properties.name: Jackson Conoco Service Station
properties.description: The Avant’s Cities Service Station is located at 220 N. Choctaw, and the Jackson Conoco Service Station is located at 121 W. Wade in El Reno, OK.

properties.name: Fort Reno
properties.description: The fort’s visitor center at 7107 Westest Cheyenne Street Fort Reno is open Monday-Friday 10:00am to 5:00pm and Saturday and Sunday 10:00am to 4:00pm and is closed on Thanksgiving, Christmas, and Northew Year’s Day. The grounds and some buildings are wheelchair accessible. Call 405-262-3987 for information.

properties.name: Provine Service Station
properties.description: Located ½ mile  west of the intersection of Highway 58 and Interstate 40 south of Hydro, OK on  historic Route 66.  The station is no longer operating, but visitors are welcome to stop and take photographs.

properties.name: McLain Rogers Park
properties.description: The McLain Rogers Park is located at the intersection of South 10th Street and Bess Rogers Drive in Clinton, OK. The park is bounded on the east by 10th Street, on the south by Jaycee Ln., on the west by 13th Street, and on the north by Opal Avenue.  Call 580-323-4572 for information.

properties.name: Y Service Station and Cafe
properties.description: The former Y Service Station and Café is located at 1733 Neptune Drive in Clinton, OK and is an automobile dealership accessible to the public.

properties.name: Beckham County Courthouse
properties.description: The Beckham County Courthouse, at 302 East Main Street in Sayre, OK, still houses government functions, and is open Monday-Friday, 8:00am to 4:00pm. The courthouse is accessible to wheelchairs. Call 580-928-3330 for information.

properties.name: West Winds Motel
properties.description: The Westest Westinds Motel is at 623 Roger Miller Boulevard. in Eastrick, OK, and is now used as a private residence.

properties.name: Route 66 Bridge over the Chicago, Rock Island, and Gulf Railroad
properties.description: The Route 66 Bridge  crosses the Chicago, Rock Island, and Gulf Railroad eight miles east of  Shamrock, TX, and remains in use as part of a frontage road for Interstate 40. The bridge stands in the arid plains eight miles east of Shamrock, five-and-a-half miles west of the Oklahoma State line, and 12 miles southeast of Westheeler.

properties.name: Tower Station and U-Drop Inn Cafe
properties.description: The Tower Station and U-Drop Inn Café is located at 101 East 12th St. at the intersection of US Highway 83 and Historic Route 66 in Shamrock, TX about six blocks north of Shamrock’s downtown commercial district.  Today, the building houses the Shamrock Chamber of Commerce, which can be reached by telephone at 806-256-2501.

properties.name: McLean Commercial Historic District, TX
properties.description: The McLean Commercial Historic District is along North Main, First, and Railroad Sts. roughly bounded by Railroad, Lowe, Second, and Gray Sts. in McLean, TX.  The former Masonic hall at 220 North Main St., now housing City Hall, is open Monday-Friday 8:00am to 12:00pm and 1:00pm to 5:00pm, and is wheelchair accessible.  Call 806-779-2481 for information. The McLean Alanreed Historical Museum at 116 South Main St. is open Tuesday-Friday 10:00am to 12:00pm and 1:00pm to 4:00pm March to December, and is wheelchair accessible.  It is free and accepts donations.  Call 806-779-2731 for information.  The Devil’s Rope Museum at 100 Kingsley St. is not in the historic district but is a good local stop that houses the Texas Old Route 66 Museum.  The museum is open Monday-Friday, 9:00am to 5:00pm and Saturday 10:00am to 4:00pm from March 1 to December 1, and is wheelchair accessible.  It is free and accepts donations.  Call 806-779-2225 for information.

properties.name: McLean Commercial Historic District, TX
properties.description: The McLean Commercial Historic District is along North Main, First, and Railroad Sts. roughly bounded by Railroad, Lowe, Second, and Gray Sts. in McLean, TX. Call 806-779-2225 for information.

properties.name: Route 66, SH 207 to Interstate 40
properties.description: This section of Route 66 is in the vicinity of Conway, TX and is labeled locally as Texas Farm Rd.  2161.  Access from the east is from State Highway 207/County Rd.  N and from the west is from Interstate 40 exit 89.

properties.name: Ranchotel
properties.description: The Ranchotel is at 2501 West Sixth Ave. in Amarillo, TX and is currently used as private apartments.

properties.name: U.S. Route 66-Sixth Street Historic District
properties.description: The U.S Route 66-Sixth Street Historic District runs for 13 blocks along 6th St. between Georgia and Forrest Avenues west of downtown Amarillo, TX. Restaurants and antique stores line the street. The district hosts a number of festivals throughout the summer.

properties.name: U.S. Route 66-Sixth Street Historic District
properties.description: The U.S Route 66-Sixth Street Historic District runs for 13 blocks along 6th St. between Georgia and Forrest Avenues west of downtown Amarillo, TX. Restaurants and antique stores line the street. The district hosts a number of festivals throughout the summer.

properties.name: Vega Motel
properties.description: The Vega Motel is located at 1005 Vega Blvd. in Vega, TX. Call 806-267-2205 for room availability.

properties.name: Glenrio Historic District
properties.description: The Glenrio Historic District includes the Historic Route 66 roadbed, also called State Loop 504, and properties north of it in Glenrio, TX and NM.

properties.name: Blue Swallow Motel
properties.description: The Blue Swallow Motel is located at 815 East Route 66 Blvd. in Tucumcari, NM. Visitors can still spend the night at the motel.

properties.name: Richardson Store
properties.description: The Richardson Store is located between the Southern Pacific Railroad tracks and Route 66 at the site of the village of Montoya, NM.  It is presently vacant and closed to the public, and may be viewed from the road.

properties.name: Park Lake Historic District
properties.description: Park Lake Historic District is located at the junction of Westill Rogers and Lake Drives in Santa Rosa, NM and is open to the public.

properties.name: Park Lake Historic District
properties.description: Park Lake Historic District is located at the junction of Westill Rogers and Lake Drives in Santa Rosa, NM and is open to the public.

properties.name: Pueblo of Santo Domingo, NM
properties.description: The Santo Domingo Pueblo is located approximately 35 miles north of Albuquerque and 25 miles south of Santa Fe, NM, via the Santo Domingo exit on Interstate 25. For more information, call 918-541-1615.

properties.name: Luna Lodge
properties.description: Luna Lodge is located at 9119 East Central Ave. in Albuquerque, NM, and is currently operating as a housing facility. Luna Lodge has been documented by the National Park Service's Historic American Engineering Record.

properties.name: Tewa Motor Lodge
properties.description: The Tewa Motor Lodge is located at 5715 Central Ave. NE in Albuquerque, NM and is still in operation as a motel.  For information on room rates and reservations, call 505-255-1632.

properties.name: De Anza Motor Lodge
properties.description: The De Anza Motor Lodge is located at 4301 Central Ave. Northeast in Albuquerque, NM.  The lodge is not operating and is accessible only for viewing from the public right of way.

properties.name: Northob Hill Shopping Center
properties.description: The Nob Hill Shopping Center is located at the corner of Central Ave. and Carlisle Blvd. in Albuquerque, NM’s Nob Hill district. Visitors will find a number of restaurants, specialty shops, and services.

properties.name: Jones Motor Company
properties.description: The Jones Motor Company, now Kelly’s Brew Pub, is located at 3222 Central Ave. SE in Albuquerque, NM.  It is open 7 days a week. For restaurant hours, call 505-262-2739.

properties.name: Barelas-South Fourth Street Historic District
properties.description: The Barelas-South Fourth Street Historic District is located along 4th St. from Stover Ave. to Bridge St. south of downtown Albuquerque, NM. A number of shops, restaurants, and other businesses in the dictrict are open to the public.

properties.name: Barelas-South Fourth Street Historic District
properties.description: The Barelas-South Fourth Street Historic District is located along 4th St. from Stover Ave. to Bridge St. south of downtown Albuquerque, NM. A number of shops, restaurants, and other businesses in the dictrict are open to the public.

properties.name: KiMo Theater
properties.description: The KiMo Theater is located at 423 Central Ave. NW in Albuquerque, NM. The theater operates Tuesday-Friday 8:30am to 4:30pm, Saturday 11:00am to 5:00pm. It is open to the public for self-guided tours from 9:00am to 4:00pm. Today, the theater seats 650 people and operates as a lively performance venue. Guided tours are available by appointment only and can be arranged by calling 505-768-3522. To obtain information about performances, call 505-768-3544 or visit the City of Albuquerque’s website. The KiMo Theater has been recorded by the National Park Service's Historic American Buildings Survey.

properties.name: Maisel's Indian Trading Post
properties.description: Maisel’s Indian Trading Post is located at 510 Central Ave. SW in Albuquerque, NM right near the intersection of Historic US 66 and 5th St. NW. It is open Monday-Friday 9:00am-5:00pm. For further information, call 505-242-6526.

properties.name: New Mexico Madonna of the Trail
properties.description: The New Mexico Madonna of the Trail is located at the intersection of Marble Avenue and Fourth Street in a small park on the grounds of the Federal Courthouse in Albuquerque, NM.

properties.name: El Vado Auto Court Motel
properties.description: The El Vado Auto Court Motel is located at 2500 Central Ave. SW in Albuquerque, NM and is currently closed to the public.

properties.name: Rio Puerco Bridge
properties.description: The Rio Puerco Bridge is located off of and parallel to Interstate 40 at exit 140 west of Albuquerque, NM.  A post-1937 alignment of Route 66, now used as a frontage road, is east of the bridge and reconnects with the interstate at exit 149. Visitors can walk across the bridge.

properties.name: Pueblo of Laguna
properties.description: The Pueblo of Laguna is approximately 45 miles west of Albuquerque, NM, off Interstate 40 along the San Jose River.  A main tourist destination is Street Joseph Church at 1 Friar Road  The church is wheelchair accessible and is generally open to visitors 9:00am to 3:00pm Monday-Friday, but for more information call 505-552-9330.  Large festivals open to the public occur annually on September 19 and March 19, and other events, both public and private, occur throughout the year.  Much of the pueblo is private, and photography, drawing, and audio/video taping are not generally allowed, but visitors interested in seeking permission for these activities or to hike or drive in tribal areas should call 505-552-6654 or look for more information on the Pueblo of Laguna website  and the State of Northew Mexico Tourism Department website. For information about the Dancing Eastagle Casino and Travel Center visit its website.

properties.name: Bowlin's Old Crater Trading Post
properties.description: Bowlin’s Old Crater Trading Post is at 7650 Old Route 66, which is now the frontage road for Interstate 40 one-and-a-half miles north of Bluewater, NM.  The building is used to mount bill boards, and the interior is not accessible.

properties.name: Roy T. Herman's Garage and Service Station
properties.description: Roy T. Herman’s Garage and Service Station is located on State Road 122, 150 yards west of the I-40 Exit 53 at Thoreau, NM.

properties.name: Fort Westingate Historic District
properties.description: Fort Westingate is approximately 12 miles southeast of Gallop, NM.  To reach it, take Interstate 40 exit 33 for Highway 400 toward McGaffey; the fort will be visible along the road after it reaches the mountains.  Historic Fort Westingate is behind a fence; to seek access, call Westilbert Dempsey of the Westingate Eastlementary School at 505-488-6421.

properties.name: Harvey House Railroad Depot
properties.description: The Harvey House Railroad Depot, which now houses the Route 66 Mother Road Museum, is located at 681 North First Ave. in Barstow, CA. The museum is open Friday-Sunday from 11:00am to 4:00pm. Admission is free. Contact the museum to confirm hours of operation at 760-255-1890, toll free at 877-997-8366 or through the museum's website. The depot has been recorded by the National Park Service's Historic American Buildings Survey.

properties.name: El Rancho Hotel
properties.description: The El Rancho Hotel is located at 1000 East 66 on the corner of Route 66 and Ford Dr. in Gallup, NM. When approaching from I-40, take exit 22 and turn south onto Ford Drive/Miyamura. The hotel has both overnight accommodations and a restaurant. For information, call the hotel at 505-863-9311, or visit the hotel's website.

properties.name: Querino Canyon Bridge
properties.description: The Querino Canyon Bridge crosses Querino Canyon 3.8 miles southwest of Houck, AZ as part of Old Highway 66.

properties.name: Painted Desert Inn
properties.description: The Painted Desert Inn is located in the northern section of Petrified Forest National Park in Petrified Forest, AZ. It has been designated a National Historic Landmark. Click here for the National Historic Landmark registration file: text and photos. The inn is now a museum open Monday-Sunday 9:00am to 5:00pm every day except Christmas. Guided tours are also available with special Halloween tours that focus on the purported ghosts said to haunt the inn. Times vary from season to season.  The park has an entrance fee but no additional fee is charged to visit the inn. Call 928-524-6228 for more information on visiting Petrified Forest National Park and the inn or go to the park website , or visit the park’s Painted Desert Inn website or call the inn directly at 928-524-3522. The Painted Desert Inn has been documented by the National Park Service’s Historic American Buildings Survey.

properties.name: Westigwam Village Motel #6
properties.description: Wigwam Village Motel #6 is located at 811 West Hopi Dr. in Holbrook, AZ.  For reservations contact 928-524-3048 or visit the Wigwam Motel website.  Each teepee has a private bathroom with toilet and shower, a television, and air conditioner. Keeping with the authenticity of the original motel, there is no ice machine, but if requested, staff will fill a small ice bucket for customers.

properties.name: La Posada Historic District
properties.description: La Posada Historic District, now La Posada Inn and Gardens, is at 303 E. Second St. /Route 66 in Winslow, AZ.  The district includes the hotel, gardens, museum, trading post, and dining.  Call 928-289-4366 for information or visit the La Posada Inn and Gardens website.

properties.name: Westalnut Canyon Bridge
properties.description: The Walnut Canyon Bridge is one mile northwest of Winona, AZ, and crosses Walnut Canyon on a former alignment of the Townsend-Winona Road/County Road 394 just north of the current alignment.  A pullout provides a place to park and view the bridge; west of the bridge is North Copley Road and east of it is Bridge Road, both which run north from the Townsend-Winona Road.

properties.name: Railroad Addition Historic District and Boundary Increase
properties.description: The Railroad Addition Historic District includes portions of Santa Fe Ave./Route 66, Aspen Ave., Leroux St., and San Francisco St. in Flagstaff, AZ and is bounded by Birch Ave., the Santa Fe Railroad tracks, Beaver St., and Agassiz St.  The Flagstaff Visitor Center in the old train station at 1 East Route 66 is open Monday-Saturday 8:00am to 5:00pm and Sunday 9:00am to 4:00pm; it is wheelchair accessible and admission is free.  For information, call 928-774-9541 or 800-842-7293 or visit its website to find out more about what to see and do and where to stay and eat.  For information on staying at the historic Hotel Monte Vista, see the hotel’s website.  For information on the DuBeau International Hostel, visit its website.

properties.name: Railroad Addition Historic District and Boundary Increase
properties.description: The Railroad Addition Historic District includes portions of Santa Fe Ave./Route 66, Aspen Ave., Leroux St., and San Francisco St. in Flagstaff, AZ and is bounded by Birch Ave., the Santa Fe Railroad tracks, Beaver St., and Agassiz St.  The Flagstaff Visitor Center in the old train station at 1 East Route 66 is open Monday-Saturday 8:00am to 5:00pm and Sunday 9:00am to 4:00pm; it is wheelchair accessible and admission is free.  For information, call 928-774-9541 or 800-842-7293 or visit its website to find out more about what to see and do and where to stay and eat.  For information on staying at the historic Hotel Monte Vista, see the hotel’s website.  For information on the DuBeau International Hostel, visit its website.

properties.name: Seligman Historic District
properties.description: Seligman Historic District is located in Seligman, AZ. The district is roughly bounded by First and Lamport Streets and Picacho and Railroad Avenues.  Chino Street, now renamed Historic Route 66, is the main east-west artery, and Main Street, the primary north-south street in the district. The 1926 alignment of Route 66 begins at the corner of Lamport Street and East Railroad Avenue, and extends along East Railroad Avenue to Main Street then north on Main Street to the corner of Main and Chino Streets.

properties.name: Peach Springs Trading Post
properties.description: The Peach Springs Trading Post is at 863 Highway 66 in Peach Springs, AZ and is used as offices for the Hualapai Tribal Forestry, Wildlife Conservation, and Game and Fish.

properties.name: Schoolhouse at Truxton Canyon Training School
properties.description: The Schoolhouse at Truxton Canyon Training School is on the northwest side of Route 66 along Music Mountain Circle in Valentine, AZ. It is currently closed to the public for renovations, but can be viewed from the road. The Hualapai Tribal Nation plans to reopen the building as a community center and offices.

properties.name: Kingman Commercial Historic District
properties.description: The Kingman Commercial Historic District encompasses nine properties on the 300 and 400 blocks of East Andy Devine Ave. in Kingman, AZ.  The Hotel Brunswick, at 315 East Andy Devine Ave., offers overnight accommodations and a restaurant and bar open Monday-Friday 11:00am to 2:00pm and Monday-Saturday 5:00pm to 9:00pm.  Call 928-718-1800 for more information. Though not in the historic district, the Powerhouse Visitors Center at 120 Andy Devine Ave. is a good first stop and provides maps for walking tours of historic downtown Kingman.  The Visitors Center is free, open daily from 8:00am to 5:00pm, and wheelchair accessible.  Call 928-753-6106 or visit the Visitor Center’s website for more information.  Within the Visitors Center is the Historic Route 66 Museum.  The museum is open daily from 9:00am to 5:00pm, costs $3 for seniors and $4 for other people, and is wheelchair accessible.  Call 928-753-9889 for information, or visit the museum’s website.

The Visitors Center is free, open daily from 8:00am to 5:00pm, and wheelchair accessible.  Call 928-753-6106 or visit the Visitor Center’s website for more information.  Within the Visitors Center is the Historic Route 66 Museum.  The museum is open daily from 9:00am to 5:00pm, costs $3 for seniors and $4 for other people, and is wheelchair accessible.  Call 928-753-9889 for information, or visit the museum’s website.

properties.name: Durlin Hotel
properties.description: The Durlin Hotel, now the Oatman Hotel, is located at 181 Main Street in Oatman, AZ. The bar and restaurant are open to the public Monday-Friday 10:00am to 6:00pm, Saturday and Sunday, 8:00am to 6:00pm. The museum is temporarily closed. For information, call the hotel at 928-768-4408.

properties.name: Old Trails Bridge
properties.description: The Old Trails Bridge is several hundred feet south of Interstate 40 where it crosses the Colorado River at Topock, AZ.  To park and view the bridge, take the Interstate 40 exit for Park Moabi, the last California exit from the west and the first from the east.  Signs direct visitors to the park.  Follow the Park Moabi Eastntrance Road north to its intersection with the National Trails Highway/Park Moabi Road then turn right.  The first vantage point is from an old brick bridge nearly a mile from the intersection.  Visitors can park on the side of the road and walk down the bridge top.  The second vantage point is nearly two miles from the intersection.  Visitors should continue along the National Trails Highway/Park Moabi Road past the first vantage point and intersection with Interstate 40; then look for a historic concrete billboard and adjacent pullout pad.  This location provides the best view of the bridge.

properties.name: Aztec Hotel
properties.description: The Aztec Hotel is located at 311 West Foothill Blvd. in Monrovia, CA. The hotel has 44 rooms and the complex includes the Mayan Room Restaurant, banquet facilities, and a courtyard.  Contact the hotel at 626-358-3231.

properties.name: Foothill Boulevard Milestone
properties.description: The Foothill Boulevard Milestone is just south of 1308 East Colorado Blvd., west of the intersection with Holliston Ave. in Pasadena, CA.

properties.name: Howard Motor Company Building
properties.description: The Howard Motor Company Building is at 1285 East Colorado Blvd. in Pasadena, CA.  It is currently vacant and closed to the public, but is easy to view from public right of ways.

properties.name: Colorado Street Bridge
properties.description: The Colorado Street Bridge spans the Arroyo Seco as part of Colorado Blvd. just south of the Ventura Freeway and between North San Rafael Ave. and North Orange Grove Blvd. in Pasadena, CA.  To view the bridge from below, take West Holly St. west from North Orange Grove Blvd. and then turn left on Arroyo Dr., which joins with North Arroyo Blvd. to pass below the bridge.  The local advocacy group, Pasadena Heritage, hosts a summer festival on the Colorado Street Bridge, closing the bridge to vehicular traffic.  To learn more about the bridge and festival, visit Pasadena Heritage’s website.

properties.name: Bekins Storage Co.
properties.description: The Bekins Storage Co. Roof Sign is a rooftop sign at 511 South Fair Oaks Ave. in Pasadena, CA.

properties.name: Rialto Theatre
properties.description: The Rialto Theatre is at 1019-1023 Fair Oaks Ave. in South Pasadena, CA.  It ceased regular movie showings some years ago, and now hosts only special events or screenings.

properties.name: Albuquerque Pig and Calf Lunch
properties.description: Pig and Calf Lunch, now the Pita Pit, is located at at 2106 Central Ave. SE, in Albuquerque, NM. It is open from 10:00am to 3:00am Monday through Friday, from 11:00am to 3:00am on Saturdays, and from 11:00am to 12:00am on Sundays. For information, visit the Pita Pit website or call 505-242-7482. The building is wheelchair accessible.

properties.name: The Cottage Bakery
properties.description: The Cottage Bakery (currently LA Underground) is at 2000 Central Ave. SE, Albuquerque, NM. It is open from 11:00am to 9:00pm Monday-Saturday and 12:00 to 6:00pm on Sunday. The entrance has a small step and is not wheelchair accessible.

properties.name: Broadway Theater and Commercial District
properties.description: The Broadway Theater and Commercial District includes approximately seven blocks along South Broadway in Los Angeles, CA; its northern boundary is midway between West Second St. and West Third St. and the southern boundary is between West Ninth St. and West Olympic St.  The Los Angeles Conservancy offers walking tours of the district for a fee on Saturday at 10:00am. Call 213-430-4209 or visit this website for information.  The Bradbury Building at 304 South Broadway is open Sunday-Saturday from 9:00am to 5:00pm.  Call 213-626-1893 for information.  The Los Angeles Theatre at 615 South Broadway is used for screenings and other special events, and is available for booking.  Call 213-629-2939 for information or visit its website.  The Million Dollar Theater at 307 South Broadway hosts special events and location filming.  Call 213-617-3600 for information or visit its website.  The Orpheum Theatre at 842 South Broadway still hosts live performances, special screenings, and other events, and is available for location filming.  Call 877-677-4386 or visit its website.

properties.name: Westigwam Village #7
properties.description: Wigwam Village #7, now the Wigwam Motel, is located at 2728 W. Foothill Blvd., Rialto/San Bernadino, CA. For information, visit the Wigwam Motel website or call 909-875-3005. The property is wheelchair accessible and pet friendly.

properties.name: Santo Domingo Trading Post
properties.description: The Santo Domingo Trading Post sits at the juncture of Indian Service Routes 88 and 841, off NM 22, exit 259 on Interstate 25, about halfway between Santa Fe and Albuquerque, NM. It is adjacent to the Kewa station of New Mexico’s Rail Runner, a light rail system easily accessible from Santa Fe or Albuquerque. The building is currently closed to the public. Photographing the building is permissible, but please do not take photos of other buildings, landscape, or individuals on Pueblo land without permission.

properties.name: The Circle Theater
properties.description: The Circle Theater, now the Circle Cinema, is located at 10 S. Lewis Ave., Tulsa, OK, and can be reached at 918-585-3504. Showtimes are available via phone at 918-592-FILM, or online on the Circle Cinema website. The theater is wheelchair accessible.

properties.name: Acoma Curio Shop
properties.description: The Acoma Curio Shop is located at 1090 State Road 124, San Fidel, NM 87049, on historic Route 66 about 15 miles east of Grants. The building is currently not open to the public.

properties.name: Route 66
properties.description: U.S. Highway 66 -- popularly known as Route 66 or the Mother Road -- holds a special place in American consciousness and evokes images of simpler times, mom and pop businesses, and the icons of a mobile nation on the road. This travel itinerary aids the public to visit the historic places that recall those images and experiences that are reminders of our past and evidence of the influence of the automobile. The Route 66 Discover Our Shared Heritage Travel Itinerary was produced by the National Park Service's Heritage Education Services and the National Park Service Route 66 Corridor Preservation Program, in partnership with the American Express and World Monuments Fund Sustainable Tourism Initiative and the National Conference of State Historic Preservation Officers.

properties.name: Arroyo Seco Parkway
properties.description: The Arroyo Seco Parkway (California State Route 110) runs northeasterly from the Four-Level Interchange with U.S. 101 just outside downtown Los Angeles (mile post 23.69) to East Glenarm St. in Pasadena (mile post 31.89), CA. It is a National Civil Engineering Landmark, a National Scenic Byway, and the first of just two California Historic Parkways (the other being S.R. 163 through Balboa Park in San Diego). In 2011, the Parkway and associated features were listed in the National Register of Historic Places as the Arroyo Seco Parkway Historic District. Also of interest is N. Figueroa St., which parallels much of the Parkway just to the west. Figueroa carried the previous alignment of Route 66 beginning in 1931, and after completion of the Parkway was Alternate 66. This is the main street of downtown Highland Park (a district of Los Angeles) with destinations associated with Route 66 to visit and explore.  Traveling both today provides telling views of two different historical experiences along the Mother Road in Los Angeles and the Arroyo Seco region of Southern California.

properties.name: Broadway Theater and Commercial District
properties.description: The Broadway Theater and Commercial District includes approximately seven blocks along South Broadway in Los Angeles, CA; its northern boundary is midway between West Second St. and West Third St. and the southern boundary is between West Ninth St. and West Olympic St.  The Los Angeles Conservancy offers walking tours of the district for a fee on Saturday at 10:00am. Call 213-430-4209 or visit this website for information.  The Bradbury Building at 304 South Broadway is open Sunday-Saturday from 9:00am to 5:00pm.  Call 213-626-1893 for information.  The Los Angeles Theatre at 615 South Broadway is used for screenings and other special events, and is available for booking.  Call 213-629-2939 for information or visit its website.  The Million Dollar Theater at 307 South Broadway hosts special events and location filming.  Call 213-617-3600 for information or visit its website.  The Orpheum Theatre at 842 South Broadway still hosts live performances, special screenings, and other events, and is available for location filming.  Call 877-677-4386 or visit its website.

properties.name: Grant Park
properties.description: Grant Park’s street address is 337 East Randolph St. in Chicago, IL.  The park is bounded on the north by Randolph Dr. and the Chicago River, on the east by Lake Michigan, on the south by McFetridge Dr., and on the west by Michigan Ave.  The park is open Monday-Friday 9:00am to 10:00pm and Saturday and Sunday 9:00am to 5:00pm, and is wheelchair accessible.  Call 312-742-7648 for information or visit the Chicago Park District Grant Park website.
